Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 143
Edition:
Quote: KINGFISH, SILVER A relative of the barracouta this fish inhabits our southern waters (he is also known as Southern Kingfish). No connection whatsoever with the Northern, or Yellowtail Kingfish. Sometimes called Hake (wrongly) and Gemfish (in Australia) ...
