Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 141
Edition:
Quote: Another so-called Kingfish occurs in southern New Zealand waters but this is no relative of <i>Seriola Grandis</i>. He is the Silver Kingfish, who is sometimes called Hake and known in Australia as Gemfish. <i>Ibid.</i> 201 Silver Kingfish and Gemfish are other names [for Southern Kingfish,<i> Jordanidia solandri</i>].
